======================================================================
PETERSEN GRAPH AND S₆ SYMMETRY
======================================================================

The 10 partitions of {0,...,5} into {3,3} are the vertices of
the Petersen graph's complement! Two partitions are Petersen-adjacent
iff they have NO common triple (i.e., |A_i ∩ A_j| ∈ {1,2}).

Actually, the PETERSEN GRAPH has 10 vertices and 15 edges.
It's the Kneser graph K(5,2) — but our 10 partitions are different.

Our 10 partitions form the vertices of the COMPLETE MULTIPARTITE
graph K_{1,1,...,1} = K₁₀... let me think about this differently.

Intersection types among 10 partitions:
  |A_i ∩ A_j| = 1: 15 pairs
  |A_i ∩ A_j| = 2: 30 pairs
  Total: 45 = C(10,2) = 45

