======================================================================
SYNTHESIS
======================================================================

The 15 α₂=4 patterns form a (10, 4, 6)-design:
  10 points (partitions), 15 blocks of size 4, each point in 6 blocks.
  This is a 2-design (BIBD) if every pair appears in λ blocks.

  Pair appearances λ: {2}
  ✓ It's a 2-(10, 4, 2) design!
  Fisher's inequality: b ≥ v: 15 ≥ 10 ✓
